  Here's what I did.  I was in the high 50's when I did this part.<br>
 <br>
  I first got another high 50's mage to come along to help.  I bought us both a KEI in Nexus, then shouted for a port to Cobalt Scar.  A druid ported us to CS.  Get a druid, not a wiz.<br>
<br>
  When you get to CS, lev and invis all three folks.  Run across CS to the tunnel to SG.  When you zone into SG, have the druid succor you across the zone.  This will put you at the WW entrance and near the swordfish area.  I paid the druid for the trip, then offered him extra if he would help us with the fight.  Druid's have an animal fear spell that works on the swordfish. <br>
<br>
  You invis up and head to the safe spot and summon pets.  Jump into the water.  When I was there, there was one single swordfish in the pool near the branch of water leaving the pool.  Both mages used 57 earth and we killed this solo fish easy.  Since we didn't want to wait for repop, I pulled another fish from further down the channel.  I was too low level and two fish came.  The druid feared them, but finally the druid went down.  The other mage and I finished both off and I looted tooth.  <br>
<br>
  I paid the druid and paid for the druid's rez.  All's well that ends well.  You'll have to check the level of the swordfish and see if they can be single pulled at your level.  Slowing, fearing, or anything else will certainly help.  Or if you are patient, you can just take the single and sit around for repop.<br>
<br>
  Elfnom<br>
