<br>
1. Yeah get a port to CS, not a Trans a port.  Pay the guy a bit extra to swim with you to SG and cast Succor to get you to the WW side.  This saves a lot of hell, almost invariably one of those seahorses on the swim path to that side see's invis.<br>
<br>
2.  Ok in you go, walk to the waterfall in the swordfish spawn room and hop on in the water.  Down you go.  The corner near the base of the waterfall is a good place to summon your pet, give it crap, and buff it up.  Obviously you want to have an EB item/use a waterstone here.<br>
<br>
3.  Now, CAREFULLY swim up near the top, and look on the left. There's a sort of small ledge off the pool embankment pretty near where you are, and there's usually a swordfish right there.  Don't go proximity aggroing it - getting hit is NOT helpful here.  Just target it.  Swim back down to your little waterfall hideyhole at the bottom.<br>
<br>
4.  Now pull the swordfish - I used my white ceramic ring &lt;great pull toy without having to take up a spell slot&gt;, you can use whatever really as long as it's very low aggro.  You want the fish to stick to your pet when it comes. It'll take a sec, pathing is odd - but eventually you'll see him coming at ya - send pet in.  You're going to need to use pet healies several times most likely here - this guy has a fair chunk of hps.  I used 4 Firebolt of Tallon's as well - but be careful here - you do NOT want to overnuke and have a pissed off fish on you - could be game over right there ;)   You should have a fairly tough fight but nothing ridiculous.<br>
<br>
5.  Loot, if you're unlucky rinse repeat heh - I had to kill 3 of the damn things to get a tooth.  Spawn time seems to be somewhat over 40 minutes.<br>
<br>
6.  Good luck :) <br>
